tweet: Kudos to Logan for his forecasts on a quick housing rebound.  I felt housing would be fine, but I've been more concerned about the longer term impacts of COVID.
Hopefully the actions taken on July 2nd will make a difference (Close bars, indoor restaurants, require masks).   Sadly I still see too many people ignoring the mask rules.

The people behaving responsibly will slow any exponential growth.  However the people behaving irresponsibly will keep the responsible people suppressed economically for a longer period - and that could lead to significant long term damage that is hard to forecast.

By Request, and Just For Fun: Stock Market as Barometer of Policy Success   If the S&P returns 29.5% from today until the end of Mr. Trump's current term (in January 2021), that would match the gains under Mr. Obama's first term.
